  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Countless ballads immortalize the long neck, the scarlet <span class=\"fontstyle0\">beak and the white plumage (or sometimes blacker than a moonless night) that distinguish the Swans, and they, with great dignity, bask in this poetic aura without embarrassment. These Anseri are extremely vain and aware of the charm they exert on others. The most desired courtesans and the most elusive con artists are Swans, and although </span>their tendency towards manipulation is well known from <span class=\"fontstyle0\">the Avian Islands to the capital of the Empire, powerful nobles and common merchants alike continue to fall prey to their plots. Swans are social for the same reasons that Foxes are, but unlike them they also have a constant need to be fondled, revered and confirmed in their being irresistible. Nothing scares a Swan more than growing old (what a tragedy to lose the regal bearing that nature and youth had given them!) or seriously falling in love with someone: when a Swan binds to a partner, they become very devoted, caring and faithful, often totally changing their life, even when it means abandoning ease and prestige.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Increase in Ability Scores.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Your <span class=\"fontstyle0\">Constitution </span>score increases by 1 and your <span class=\"fontstyle0\">Charisma </span>score increases by 2.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Age.</strong></em> </span>An Anseri reaches maturity at around 12 years <span class=\"fontstyle0\">of age and is immediately considered independent. They have an average lifespan of around 60 years.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Speed.</strong></em> </span>Your base speed on the ground is 15 feet, your flying </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">speed is 30 feet, and your swimming speed is 35 feet.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Size. </strong></em></span>A Swan can reach a height of between 4 1/4 feet and <span class=\"fontstyle0\">5 1/4 feet, and weigh between 65 lbs and 90 lbs.</span>  <span class=\"fontstyle2\">Your size is Medium.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Beauty.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You have proficiency Performance. </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.ZLta2Wjm3OsgNAk0]{Wings}</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.DO8bJUsTURvkwDVu]{Pecking}</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.9tSBClRGsMUrRPQw]{Clumsy}<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.5a9slEU5BRDefy5v]{Internal Compass}</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.p9KCNI8RdCDY7zkg]{Fiery Spirit}</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.A8s7NDJ3WeiNWtrh]{Webbed Legs}</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[world.species-features.6AF4ovTKSQZUiP0e]{Relentless Tenacity}</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em><strong>Instinct of Familia, Migrator (Prey):</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle4\">“I am looking for the best environment for me, I shy away from hostile environments”</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle4\"><em><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Instinct of Species, Noble: </span></strong></em><span class=\"fontstyle2\">“I can fly higher than ordinary people”.</span> <br style=\"font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;orphans:2;text-align:-webkit-auto;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\" /></span></p>",
      "chat": "",
